<executable>
  <category>Filtering</category>
  <index>1</index>
  <title>MRI Bias Field Correction</title>
  <description>
Correction of the MRI Bias Field generated during a MRI.

ITK filter initially developed and implemented by Martin STYNER in [3]. To estimate the bias field, he uses Legendre polynomials. The 1+1 evolutionary optimizer searches for the best parameters of a Legendre polynomial (bias field estimate) which minimizes the total energy value of each image.

Load the volume you want to process in Slicer: File->Add Volume
Load the MRI Bias Field Correction Filter Module: Modules->Filtering->MRI Bias Field Correction Filter
Enter the mean value of the 2 tissues which are the most present in the volume.
Check if you want to use or not a mask for the correction (recommended)
Set the volume you loaded as “Input Volume”
Choose an output volume
Click on apply
  </description>
